{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":896,"text":"So I'm a neurosurgeon."},{"time":3746,"text":"And like most of my colleagues,"},{"time":5673,"text":"I have to deal, every day,\nwith human tragedies."},{"time":10549,"text":"I realize how your life can change\nfrom one second to the other"},{"time":15378,"text":"after a major stroke\nor after a car accident."},{"time":20045,"text":"And what is very frustrating\nfor us neurosurgeons"},{"time":23807,"text":"is to realize that unlike\nother organs of the body,"},{"time":28451,"text":"the brain has very little\nability for self-repair."},{"time":33211,"text":"And after a major injury\nof your central nervous system,"},{"time":38365,"text":"the patients often remain\nwith a severe handicap."},{"time":43203,"text":"And that's probably\nthe reason why I've chosen"},{"time":45440,"text":"to be a functional neurosurgeon."}]},{"cues":[{"time":49144,"text":"What is a functional neurosurgeon?"},{"time":51978,"text":"It's a doctor who is trying to improve\na neurological function"},{"time":56362,"text":"through different surgical strategies."},{"time":60066,"text":"You've certainly heard of\none of the famous ones"},{"time":62400,"text":"called deep brain stimulation,"},{"time":65230,"text":"where you implant an electrode\nin the depths of the brain"},{"time":69386,"text":"in order to modulate a circuit of neurons"},{"time":72986,"text":"to improve a neurological function."},{"time":75330,"text":"It's really an amazing technology"},{"time":77420,"text":"in that it has improved\nthe destiny of patients"},{"time":80811,"text":"with Parkinson's disease,"},{"time":82657,"text":"with severe tremor, with severe pain."},{"time":86870,"text":"However, neuromodulation\ndoes not mean neuro-repair."},{"time":93301,"text":"And the dream of functional neurosurgeons"},{"time":95632,"text":"is to repair the brain."},{"time":99222,"text":"I think"},{"time":100643,"text":"that we are approaching this dream."}]},{"cues":[{"time":102502,"text":"And I would like to show you"},{"time":105161,"text":"that we are very close to this."},{"time":108022,"text":"And that with a little bit of help,"},{"time":111157,"text":"the brain is able to help itself."}]},{"cues":[{"time":116516,"text":"So the story started 15 years ago."},{"time":119156,"text":"At that time, I was a chief resident"},{"time":121200,"text":"working days and nights\nin the emergency room."},{"time":124619,"text":"I often had to take care\nof patients with head trauma."},{"time":129193,"text":"You have to imagine that when a patient\ncomes in with a severe head trauma,"},{"time":133678,"text":"his brain is swelling"},{"time":136001,"text":"and he's increasing\nhis intracranial pressure."},{"time":139716,"text":"And in order to save his life,"},{"time":141969,"text":"you have to decrease\nthis intracranial pressure."},{"time":144801,"text":"And to do that,"},{"time":145976,"text":"you sometimes have to remove\na piece of swollen brain."},{"time":150587,"text":"So instead of throwing away\nthese pieces of swollen brain,"},{"time":154959,"text":"we decided with Jean-François Brunet,"},{"time":157472,"text":"who is a colleague of mine, a biologist,"},{"time":159409,"text":"to study them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":161379,"text":"What do I mean by that?"},{"time":163174,"text":"We wanted to grow cells\nfrom these pieces of tissue."},{"time":168484,"text":"It's not an easy task."},{"time":170577,"text":"Growing cells from a piece of tissue"},{"time":172966,"text":"is a bit the same as growing\nvery small children"},{"time":176449,"text":"out from their family."},{"time":179689,"text":"So you need to find the right nutrients,"},{"time":182030,"text":"the warmth, the humidity"},{"time":183823,"text":"and all the nice environments\nto make them thrive."},{"time":187083,"text":"So that's exactly what we had\nto do with these cells."},{"time":190425,"text":"And after many attempts,"},{"time":192959,"text":"Jean-François did it."},{"time":195372,"text":"And that's what he saw\nunder his microscope."}]},{"cues":[{"time":199691,"text":"And that was, for us, a major surprise."},{"time":202412,"text":"Why?"},{"time":203587,"text":"Because this looks exactly the same\nas a stem cell culture,"},{"time":208453,"text":"with large green cells\nsurrounding small, immature cells."},{"time":215168,"text":"And you may remember from biology class"},{"time":218446,"text":"that stem cells are immature cells,"},{"time":221981,"text":"able to turn into any type\nof cell of the body."},{"time":227423,"text":"The adult brain has stem cells,\nbut they're very rare"},{"time":232075,"text":"and they're located\nin deep and small niches"},{"time":236478,"text":"in the depths of the brain."},{"time":238519,"text":"So it was surprising to get\nthis kind of stem cell culture"},{"time":242245,"text":"from the superficial part\nof swollen brain we had"},{"time":244628,"text":"in the operating theater."}]},{"cues":[{"time":246269,"text":"And there was another\nintriguing observation:"},{"time":249890,"text":"Regular stem cells\nare very active cells --"},{"time":254140,"text":"cells that divide, divide,\ndivide very quickly."},{"time":258409,"text":"And they never die,\nthey're immortal cells."},{"time":261407,"text":"But these cells behave differently."},{"time":264663,"text":"They divide slowly,"},{"time":266870,"text":"and after a few weeks of culture,"},{"time":268894,"text":"they even died."},{"time":271321,"text":"So we were in front of a strange\nnew cell population"},{"time":274997,"text":"that looked like stem cells\nbut behaved differently."}]},{"cues":[{"time":279052,"text":"And it took us a long time\nto understand where they came from."},{"time":283520,"text":"They come from these cells."},{"time":286550,"text":"These blue and red cells are called\ndoublecortin-positive cells."},{"time":292195,"text":"All of you have them in your brain."},{"time":295353,"text":"They represent four percent\nof your cortical brain cells."},{"time":299857,"text":"They have a very important role\nduring the development stage."},{"time":303953,"text":"When you were fetuses,"},{"time":306457,"text":"they helped your brain to fold itself."},{"time":310120,"text":"But why do they stay in your head?"},{"time":313371,"text":"This, we don't know."},{"time":315414,"text":"We think that they may\nparticipate in brain repair"},{"time":318660,"text":"because we find them\nin higher concentration"},{"time":322148,"text":"close to brain lesions."},{"time":323324,"text":"But it's not so sure."},{"time":325867,"text":"But there is one clear thing --"},{"time":328236,"text":"that from these cells,"},{"time":329857,"text":"we got our stem cell culture."},{"time":333363,"text":"And we were in front\nof a potential new source of cells"},{"time":336021,"text":"to repair the brain."},{"time":338004,"text":"And we had to prove this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":339585,"text":"So to prove it,"},{"time":340760,"text":"we decided to design\nan experimental paradigm."},{"time":344632,"text":"The idea was to biopsy a piece of brain"},{"time":347879,"text":"in a non-eloquent area of the brain,"},{"time":350602,"text":"and then to culture the cells"},{"time":352337,"text":"exactly the way Jean-François\ndid it in his lab."},{"time":355148,"text":"And then label them, to put color in them"},{"time":358067,"text":"in order to be able\nto track them in the brain."},{"time":361295,"text":"And the last step was to re-implant them"},{"time":363448,"text":"in the same individual."},{"time":365255,"text":"We call these"},{"time":366430,"text":"autologous grafts -- autografts."}]},{"cues":[{"time":369602,"text":"So the first question we had,"},{"time":372069,"text":"\"What will happen if we re-implant\nthese cells in a normal brain,"},{"time":377334,"text":"and what will happen\nif we re-implant the same cells"},{"time":380216,"text":"in a lesioned brain?\""},{"time":381463,"text":"Thanks to the help\nof professor Eric Rouiller,"},{"time":384876,"text":"we worked with monkeys."}]},{"cues":[{"time":387414,"text":"So in the first-case scenario,"},{"time":389878,"text":"we re-implanted the cells\nin the normal brain"},{"time":393407,"text":"and what we saw is that they completely\ndisappeared after a few weeks,"},{"time":398466,"text":"as if they were taken from the brain,"},{"time":401444,"text":"they go back home,"},{"time":402979,"text":"the space is already busy,"},{"time":404559,"text":"they are not needed there,\nso they disappear."}]},{"cues":[{"time":407780,"text":"In the second-case scenario,"},{"time":409782,"text":"we performed the lesion,"},{"time":411037,"text":"we re-implanted exactly the same cells,"},{"time":414201,"text":"and in this case, the cells remained --"},{"time":418298,"text":"and they became mature neurons."},{"time":421824,"text":"And that's the image of what\nwe could observe under the microscope."},{"time":425635,"text":"Those are the cells\nthat were re-implanted."},{"time":428839,"text":"And the proof they carry,"},{"time":430810,"text":"these little spots, those\nare the cells that we've labeled"},{"time":434011,"text":"in vitro, when they were in culture."}]},{"cues":[{"time":437755,"text":"But we could not stop here, of course."},{"time":440521,"text":"Do these cells also help a monkey\nto recover after a lesion?"},{"time":445182,"text":"So for that, we trained monkeys\nto perform a manual dexterity task."},{"time":450688,"text":"They had to retrieve\nfood pellets from a tray."},{"time":453730,"text":"They were very good at it."},{"time":455896,"text":"And when they had reached\na plateau of performance,"},{"time":459392,"text":"we did a lesion in the motor cortex\ncorresponding to the hand motion."},{"time":465711,"text":"So the monkeys were plegic,"},{"time":467592,"text":"they could not move their hand anymore."},{"time":470165,"text":"And exactly the same as humans would do,"},{"time":473743,"text":"they spontaneously recovered\nto a certain extent,"},{"time":476693,"text":"exactly the same as after a stroke."},{"time":478737,"text":"Patients are completely plegic,"},{"time":480548,"text":"and then they try to recover\ndue to a brain plasticity mechanism,"},{"time":485680,"text":"they recover to a certain extent,"},{"time":487344,"text":"exactly the same for the monkey."}]},{"cues":[{"time":489209,"text":"So when we were sure that the monkey\nhad reached his plateau"},{"time":492677,"text":"of spontaneous recovery,"},{"time":495129,"text":"we implanted his own cells."},{"time":498287,"text":"So on the left side, you see the monkey\nthat has spontaneously recovered."},{"time":505426,"text":"He's at about 40 to 50 percent\nof his previous performance"},{"time":510082,"text":"before the lesion."},{"time":512079,"text":"He's not so accurate, not so quick."},{"time":515376,"text":"And look now when we re-implant the cells:"},{"time":518859,"text":"Two months after re-implantation,\nthe same individual."}]},{"cues":[{"time":525255,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":532770,"text":"It was also very exciting results\nfor us, I tell you."},{"time":537321,"text":"Since that time, we've understood\nmuch more about these cells."},{"time":541575,"text":"We know that we can cryopreserve them,"},{"time":543995,"text":"we can use them later on."},{"time":546214,"text":"We know that we can apply them\nin other neuropathological models,"},{"time":550128,"text":"like Parkinson's disease, for example."},{"time":552121,"text":"But our dream is still\nto implant them in humans."},{"time":556469,"text":"And I really hope that I'll be able\nto show you soon"},{"time":561605,"text":"that the human brain is giving us\nthe tools to repair itself."}]},{"cues":[{"time":566623,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":567967,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":573977,"text":"Bruno Giussani: Jocelyne, this is amazing,"},{"time":577303,"text":"and I'm sure that right now, there are\nseveral dozen people in the audience,"},{"time":581078,"text":"possibly even a majority,"},{"time":582308,"text":"who are thinking, \"I know\nsomebody who can use this.\""},{"time":585080,"text":"I do, in any case."},{"time":587364,"text":"And of course the question is,"},{"time":589684,"text":"what are the biggest obstacles"},{"time":591786,"text":"before you can go\ninto human clinical trials?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":595665,"text":"Jocelyne Bloch: The biggest\nobstacles are regulations. (Laughs)"},{"time":601195,"text":"So, from these exciting results,\nyou need to fill out"},{"time":603981,"text":"about two kilograms of papers and forms"},{"time":607242,"text":"to be able to go through these\nkind of trials."}]},{"cues":[{"time":610314,"text":"BG: Which is understandable,\nthe brain is delicate, etc."}]},{"cues":[{"time":612970,"text":"JB: Yes, it is, but it takes a long time"},{"time":615352,"text":"and a lot of patience and almost\na professional team to do it, you know?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":619407,"text":"BG: If you project yourself --"},{"time":621697,"text":"having done the research"},{"time":622936,"text":"and having tried to get\npermission to start the trials,"},{"time":626905,"text":"if you project yourself out in time,"},{"time":630736,"text":"how many years before\nsomebody gets into a hospital"},{"time":634458,"text":"and this therapy is available?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":637555,"text":"JB: So, it's very difficult to say."},{"time":639714,"text":"It depends, first,\non the approval of the trial."},{"time":643672,"text":"Will the regulation allow us\nto do it soon?"},{"time":646799,"text":"And then, you have to perform\nthis kind of study"},{"time":649637,"text":"in a small group of patients."},{"time":652461,"text":"So it takes, already, a long time\nto select the patients,"},{"time":655410,"text":"do the treatment"},{"time":657340,"text":"and evaluate if it's useful\nto do this kind of treatment."},{"time":661093,"text":"And then you have to deploy\nthis to a multicentric trial."},{"time":665776,"text":"You have to really prove\nfirst that it's useful"},{"time":669962,"text":"before offering this treatment\nup for everybody."}]},{"cues":[{"time":672867,"text":"BG: And safe, of course. JB: Of course."}]},{"cues":[{"time":674780,"text":"BG: Jocelyne, thank you for coming\nto TED and sharing this."},{"time":677598,"text":"BG: Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":678773,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}